This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Demetrius Darnell Nash

records.addlTxt: Cash bail previously posted to remain. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Court ordered NO VIOLENT contact with LSA. No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed. Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Demetrius Darnell Nash in court.  Prosecuting attorney Abigail Doweiko in court under the supervision of Thomas L. Potter in court for the State of Wisconsin under the student practice rule. Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Skwierawski, Branch 41.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant.  Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant was given a referral to the Public Defender's Office. Defendant MAY be Public Defender eligible.  Additional statements made by LSA.

The case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Br. 41.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 10/21/22 @ 1p
